    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA70-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kāmammikka kaḻipaṭar kiḷavi.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This the speech [situation] of exceeding affliction when desire had increased.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA70">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            ciṟuveḷḷāṅ kurukē ciṟuveḷḷāṅ kurukē</l>
<l>            tuṟaipō kaṟuvait tūmaṭi yaṉṉa</l>
<l>            niṟaṅkiḷar tūvic ciṟuveḷḷāṅ kurukē</l>
<l>            yemmūr vantem moṇṭuṟait tuḻaiic</l>
<l>            ciṉaikkeḷiṟ ṟārkaiyai yavarūrp peyarti </l>
<l>            yaṉaiyavaṉ piṉaiyō perumaṟa viyaiyō</l>
<l>            vāṅkaṭ ṭīmpuṉa līṅkaṭ parakkuṅ</l>
<l>            kaḻaṉi nallūr makiḻnarkke</l>
<l>            ṉiḻainekiḻ paruvaral ceppā tōyē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Little white egret! Little white egret!</l>
<l rend="indent">Feathers resplendent in colour like a clean garment</l>
<l rend="indent">from cloth that went to the ghat,</l>
<l rend="indent4">little white egret!</l>
<l>You shall come to our village, stirring our bright ghat</l>
<l>[and], full of the finned Keḷiṟu fish, return to his village.</l>
<l>Do you have that much love or are you of great forgetfulness,</l>
<l rend="indent">that you don't talk of [my] jewel-loosening suffering</l>
<l rend="indent2">to the delightful man from the good village in the paddy fields,</l>
<l rend="indent3">the sweet flood from there spreading [even] here?</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
